  "description": [
    "Renowned Pacifist Talks To Helena Audience On Recent Developments In the Communist World By the EDITOR Communisms monolithic structure which reached a high point under the brutal dictator ship as characterized the latter years of Joseph Stalin is slowly eroding under the pres sure of forces within the Soviet Union and outside its borders Rev A J Muste of New York City told an audience of more than 100 people in Helena last Friday evening Rev Muste a longtime Presbyterian minister and a leader in the Fellowship of Reconcilia tion spoke at the Methodist Church under sponsorship of the American Friends Service Quakers He was introduced Helena Attorney Charles V Huppe who recalled that more than a quart er of a century ago when as a stu dent at Columbia University in New York City he had introduced Rev Muste at a meeting of nonCommu nist student pacifists At that time Huppe said the student group in which he was active was engaged in a spirited ideological battle on the Columbia campus with the Young Communist League which during the Spanish Civil War eschewed pasi fism and was strongly activist CANNOT RECONCILE WAR WITH CHRISTIAN DOCTRINE The Presbyterian minister who"
